# Marketing Automation - Required Secrets Example
# 
# Copy this file to understand what secrets you need to configure
# in GitHub Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
#
# DO NOT commit actual secrets to the repository!

# =============================================================================
# Dev.to API
# =============================================================================
# Get your API key from: https://dev.to/settings/extensions
# Required for: Publishing blog posts to Dev.to
DEVTO_API_KEY=your_devto_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# Medium API
# =============================================================================
# Get your integration token from: https://medium.com/me/settings/security
# Required for: Publishing blog drafts to Medium
MEDIUM_API_KEY=your_medium_integration_token_here

# Optional: Your Medium user ID (will be auto-detected if not provided)
# Get via: curl -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" https://api.medium.com/v1/me
MEDIUM_USER_ID=your_medium_user_id

# =============================================================================
# Twitter/X API
# =============================================================================
# Get these from: https://developer.twitter.com/en/portal/dashboard
# Required for: Posting release announcements to Twitter/X
# You need ALL FOUR credentials

# API Key (also called Consumer Key)
TWITTER_API_KEY=your_twitter_api_key

# API Secret (also called Consumer Secret)
TWITTER_API_SECRET=your_twitter_api_secret

# Access Token
TWITTER_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_twitter_access_token

# Access Token Secret
TWITTER_ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET=your_twitter_access_token_secret

# =============================================================================
# LinkedIn API
# =============================================================================
# Get OAuth 2.0 access token from LinkedIn Developer Portal
# Create app at: https://www.linkedin.com/developers/
# Requires 'w_member_social' scope
# Note: Tokens expire after 60 days - set reminder to regenerate!
# Required for: Posting release announcements to LinkedIn
LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_linkedin_access_token

# Optional: Your LinkedIn person URN (will be auto-detected if not provided)
# Get via: curl -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" https://api.linkedin.com/v2/me
# Format: urn:li:person:XXXXXXXXX
LINKEDIN_PERSON_URN=urn:li:person:your_person_id

# =============================================================================
# GitHub (Automatically Provided)
# =============================================================================
# No configuration needed - GitHub automatically provides this token
# GITHUB_TOKEN=automatically_provided_by_github_actions

# =============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Get API keys/tokens from each platform (see links above)
# 2. Go to your GitHub repository
# 3. Navigate to: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# 4. Click "New repository secret" for each secret
# 5. Add the secret name (e.g., DEVTO_API_KEY) and value
# 6. Test the workflow with manual trigger before first release
#
# Detailed setup guide: docs/MARKETING_AUTOMATION_SETUP.md
# Quick reference: docs/MARKETING_AUTOMATION_QUICK_REF.md
#
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# Security Reminders
# =============================================================================
# ⚠️  NEVER commit this file with actual secrets!
# ⚠️  Use GitHub Secrets, not environment variables in workflows
# ⚠️  Rotate credentials regularly (LinkedIn expires every 60 days)
# ⚠️  Revoke immediately if compromised
# ⚠️  Monitor API usage for unexpected activity
# =============================================================================
